--- end of examples

Also, I have identified some of the controls. No ground-breaking
innovations here, as most of them were already handled correctly
by ddccontrol using the supplied xml file and some of them are still
unknown. There are even ones for which the xml comments tell
something but I was unable to find their effects.
The following part of this report will go through the individual
controls returned by 'ddccontrol -p' along with their effects,
equivalent osd settings, fix recommendations and some other notes.

terminology
--------
concepts I'm going to use in this report:
  trigger: write-only controls which stick to a base value and writing
    a different value carries out some action (such as reset to defaults)
  setting: read-write controls which generally return the last value
    written when read (except for margins/redirecting invalid input)
    these generally map to a monitor parameter such as brightness
  osd control: an option available through the osd menu or otherwise
    using the buttons on the monitor
  osd path: names of submenus and options in the osd menu that should
    be chosen to access an osd control, separated by slashes
    (such as: color/color tone/warm)
  persistent: a setting which keeps its value when the monitor is turned
    successively off and on (using the soft-off button on the front
    panel of the monitor)
  transient: in contrast to persistent, a setting which resets to a
    default value after an off+on combination (i.e. is volatile)
    interestingly, this usually occurs when switching on, not off
    (the monitor can also be queried when in soft-off)
  regular: if used alone, acts as transient (i.e. effects are restored
    during off+on), but if 0xb0/1 (store settings) is called after it,
    but before turning off (or on, I don't know), the new value is saved
    and is restored after an off+on combination
  IR: "Invalid response, first byte is 0x51, should be 0x6e"
    error message, which occurs quite often (so seems valid)
    (mentioned in results above)
  OK: the specified control needs no change
  FIX: needs a minor change in the xml file
  TODO: something more needs to be done

summary of controls
--------

osd controls without corresponding ddc/ci controls:
(or at least, setting them does not modify any ddc/ci controls)

  osd/h-position   (horizontal position of osd, 0-100)
  osd/v-position   (vertical position of osd, 0-100)
  osd/transparency (boolean specifying whether osd is translucent)
  osd/display time (idle time before osd closes, chosen from
                    5 sec, 10 sec, 20 sec and 200 sec)
  information      (tells the horizontal and vertical frequency,
                    screen resolution and 'PP' (which I don't know))

list of ddc/ci controls:
(controls are identified by their hex id and xml name if present)

0x04 defaults
  trigger, base:0, persistent
  1 -> reset default settings
    resets the following settings to these values
    * 0x0e coarse      90/180
    * 0x10 brightness  80/100
    * 0x12 contrast    80/100
    * 0x16 red         32/64
    * 0x18 green       32/64
    * 0x1a blue        32/64
    * 0x20 hpos        50/100
    * 0x30 vpos        35/70
    * 0x3e fine        0/31
    * 0x87 sharpness   15/25
    * 0xe0 colorpreset 0/3
    * 0xf2 gamma       0/2
    (actually it resets all settings, but these were
    the ones I reset before each test)
    it also resets some of the osd settings which do not
    have ddc/ci control equivalents
    * osd/h-position   50 
    * osd/v-position   50
    * osd/transparency Off
    * osd/display time 20 sec
    also sets a 'dirty' flag, so an auto adjustment will be
    performed when changing to a new resolution or turning off+on
    saves settings (as 0xb0/1)
    monitor led turns off for 0.5 seconds
    throws IR
  TODO: IR

0x05 defaultluma
  trigger, base: 0, regular
  1 -> reset brightness and contrast
    resets the following settings to these values
    * 0x10 brightness  80/100
    * 0x12 contrast    80/100
  OK

0x06 defaultgeom
  trigger, base: 0, partially persistent
  1 -> reset geometry settings
    osd path: setup/image reset/yes
    resets the following settings to these values
    * 0x0e coarse      90/180
    * 0x20 horizontal  50/100
    * 0x30 vertical    35/70
    * 0x3e fine        0/31
    * 0x87 sharpness   15/25
    sets the dirty flag (this is a persistent effect)
    (all other effects are regular)
    throws IR
  TODO: IR

0x08 defaultcolor
  trigger, base: 0, regular
  1 -> reset colour settings
    osd path: setup/color reset/yes
    resets the following settings to these values
    * 0x10 brightness  80/100
    * 0x12 contrast    80/100
    * 0x16 red max     32/64
    * 0x18 green max   32/64
    * 0x1a blue max    32/64
    * 0x0e colorpreset 0/3
    * 0xf2 gamma       0/2
  OK

0x0e coarse
  setting, 0-180, regular
  osd path: image/coarse
  sets the clock
  osd value is 1638 + control value (thus, real range is 1638-1818)
  OK

0x10 brightness
  setting, 0-100, regular
  osd path: picture/brightness
  OK

0x12 contrast
  setting, 0-100, regular
  osd path: picture/contrast
  OK

0x16 red
  setting, 0-64, regular
  osd path: color/color control/red
  (changes colorpreset to custom)
  OK

0x18 green
  setting, 0-64, regular
  osd path: color/color control/green
  (changes colorpreset to custom)
  OK

0x1a blue
  setting, 0-64, regular
  osd path: color/color control/blue
  (changes colorpreset to custom)
  OK

0x1e auto
  trigger, base: 0, persistent (only if finished)
  1 -> auto adjustment, slow
    equivalent to the auto button on the monitor face
    takes approximately 4.5 or 2 seconds
    (see notes at 0xe2)
    displays a progress bar
  2 -> auto adjustment, fast
    takes approximately 0.5 seconds
    displays a progress bar, but jumps from 0% to 100%
  I couldn't find any difference between the accuracy of the methods
  when the dirty flag is set, a third auto adjustment mode is invoked
  (whose speed is between these two and which has a regularly moving
  progress bar like in mode 1)
  returns 1 while adjustment is in progress
  throws IR
  FIX: add the fast mode
  TODO: IR

0x20 hpos
  setting, 0-100, regular
  osd path: image/h-position
  OK

0x30 vpos
  setting, 0-100, regular
  osd path: image/v-position
  OK

0x3e fine
  setting, 0-31, regular
  osd path: image/fine
  OK

0x60 inputsource (?)
  reported range 0-3, but sticked to 1, readonly
  based on the xml files for other models, this should
  select input source (1 for analog, 3 for digital)
  but for this model, only analog input (1) is available
  TODO: check

0x62 UNKNOWN
  setting, 0-50, regular
  factory default for this setting is 25
  after tweaking some other settings, it changed to 30
  (I don't know the exact setting that changed it)
  so it must be of some use, but I'm unable to find out
  TODO: find out

0x6c UNKNOWN
  setting, 0-255, transient -> 255
  TODO: find out

0x6e UNKNOWN
  setting, 0-255, transient -> 255
  TODO: find out

0x70 UNKNOWN
  setting, 0-255, transient -> 255
  TODO: find out

# values 0x6c, 0x6e, 0x70 make me feel that they are an RGB triplet
# xml comments state service RGB black levels
# however, I haven't noticed any effects

0x87 NEW sharpness
  setting, 0-25, regular
  osd path: image/sharpness
  this option isn't present in any of the SAM####.xml's
  specifies the sharpness of the monitor, higher means sharper
  when set below 10, screen is blurred
  when set near 25, light objects get dark contours and vice versa
  FIX: add this setting

0xb0 settings
  trigger, base: 0
  1 -> store settings
    this saves the values of regular settings to be restored after
    the monitor is turned off or changed to a different resolution
    a regular setting which is not stored resembles a transient one,
    while storing after each setting makes it like a persistent one
    I was unable to check whether it is enough to call it after
    switching off but before switching on because control 0xdc
    (magicbright) which I used for testing seemed readonly while
    the monitor was turned off
    this trigger turns the dirty flag off (disables auto adjustment
    on resolution change or power off+on)
  2 -> resets position to defaults
    resets the following settings to these values
    * 0x0e coarse      90/180
    * 0x20 horizontal  50/100
    * 0x30 vertical    35/70
    * 0x3e fine        0/31
    this is almost equivalent to control 0x06/1,
    but the sharpness is not reset
  monitor led turns off for .5 seconds (for both options)
  throws IR
  TODO: IR

0xca osd
  setting, 1-2, transient -> 2
  this setting disables the display of the osd panel
  however, the buttons work the same way
  (i.e. the menu can be still controlled if you remember the positions)
  if the menu is already displayed, it isn't removed but does
  not reappear after hiding
  also, if the menu is active but not shown, it does not show up
  when turned on, only after closing and reopening it
  though this option is present in the xml file,
  ddccontrol seems not to recognise it
  FIX: make this available

0xcc language
  setting, 1-11, persistent
  osd path: osd/language
  changing this setting switches back to first page of osd
  2 -> english (English)
  3 -> french (Français)
  4 -> german (Deutsch)
  5 -> italian (Italiano)
  9 -> russian (Русский)
  10 -> spanish (Español)
  11 -> swedish (Svenska)
  8 does nothing (keeps the old value), similarly to out-of-range values
  1, 6 and 7 map to 2 (english)
  changing this setting (even identically) saves all
  settings using 0xb0/1 (but monitor led does not blink)
  besides making this setting persistent, this also means that
  other changes meant to be transient are also saved
  this is a perhaps unwanted side-effect
  throws IR (except for 0 and 8 which do nothing)
  TODO: IR

0xd6 dpms
  setting, 1-4, transient
  enables or disables dpms standby
  1 -> on
  4 -> standby
  2 and 3 map to 4 (standby)
  throws IR
  TODO: IR

0xdc magicbright
  setting, 1-4, regular
  1 -> text
  2 -> internet
  3 -> entertain
  4 -> custom
  it is strange that values higher than 4 are permitted and kept,
  despite the reported maximum of 4
  in these modes, none of the options has a tick next to it
  on the osd magicbright box
  FIX: correct the list of options

0xe0 colorpreset
  setting, 0-3, regular
  0 -> normal or custom
  1 -> warm
  2 -> cool
  3 maps to 0
  osd values 'normal' and 'custom' seem to be impossible to
  distinguish using this control
  when writing a value of 0 (or 3), it sets mode to custom (on osd)
  and recalls the last custom mode superceded by normal/warm/cool
  (if the control was not already set to 0)
  I found no way to reset to normal using this control
  (setting r/g/b to 32/32/32 has the same effect but the osd
  still says 'custom')
  setting this also modifies values @ 0x16, 0x18, 0x1a
  also, setting those values sets this preset to 0 (custom)
  FIX: correct the list of options

0xe1 power
  setting, 0-1, difficult to tell whether it is persistent :D
  monitor power (on/off)
  has the same effect as the soft-off button on the monitor face
  0 -> off
  1 -> on
  while listed in the xml, ddccontrol still does not recognize it
  throws IR
  FIX: make it recognized
  TODO: IR

0xe2 UNKNOWN
  setting, 0-1, persistent
  this setting is persistent, but doesn't affect others
  it has to do something with the dirty flag
  when in state 0, slow auto adjust (0x1e/1) takes approx. 4.5 seconds
  when in state 1, slow auto adjust (0x1e/1) takes approx. 2 seconds
  timing of fast auto adjust (0x1e/2) seems unaffected
  if the dirty flag is turned on (using 0x04 or 0x06), an auto
  adjustment takes place on the next off+on or resolution change
  which turns the dirty flag back off
  if, however, this setting is set to 1 before the off+on or
  resolution change, the dirty flag is not processed
  that is, the auto adjustment does not occur and the status of
  the dirty flag is kept
  when it is reset to 0, if the dirty flag is on, the auto adjustment
  takes place on the next off+on or resolution change
  (it this setting is not reset to 1 meanwhile)
  TODO: check if it's the real and only effect

0xed UNKNOWN
  setting, 0-255, transient -> 99
  TODO: find out

0xee UNKNOWN
  setting, 0-255, transient -> 101
  TODO: find out

0xef UNKNOWN
  setting, 0-255, transient -> 101

# similarly to values 0x6c, 0x6e, 0x70, these values
# (0xed, 0xee, 0xef) make me feel that they are an RGB triplet
# xml comments state SAM RGB black levels
# however, I haven't noticed any effects

0xf0 UNKNOWN
  readonly (set to 3, reported max is 0)
  according to the xml, this is supposed to be the magiccolor
  setting for models that support it
  actually, this model does not
  the reported max is still quite strange
  TODO: check whether it's really magiccolor & why is max < value

0xf2 gamma
  setting, 0-2, regular
  osd path: color/gamma
  0 -> mode1
  1 -> mode2
  2 -> mode3
  FIX: correct the list of options

0xf5 NEW buttons
  setting, 0-2, transient
  0 monitor face buttons are fully functional
  1 osd can't be opened, pressing any button on the monitor face
    (except for soft-off) displays a 'MagicTune' popup instead
    of its regular function
    used by official utility to avoid changing the settings on the
    osd while it is running
    it control 0xca is used to disable the osd, this function
    will disable the buttons with no popup when they are pressed
  2 maps to 0
  FIX: add this setting

thanks
--------
Finally, let me thank the authors of ddccontrol for creating this
great software for the linux community, filling the gap for a
MagicTune port. I really like the command-line support which is
even missing from the proprietary, Windows-only version.


