I have created what I think is a support file for the Dell 2405FPW
(DELA010) lcd screen over DVI against the CVS stuff.

Based on the output of LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddccontrol -p -c -d

vvvvvvvv
ddccontrol version 0.4
Copyright 2004-2005 Oleg I. Vdovikin (oleg@...13...)
Copyright 2004-2006 Nicolas Boichat (nicolas@...3...)
This program comes with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY.
You may redistribute copies of this program under the terms of the GNU
General Public License.

Probing for available monitorsI/O warning : failed to load external
entity "/usr/local/share/ddccontrol-db/monitor/DELA010.xml"
Document not parsed successfully.
...
Detected monitors :
 - Device: pci:02:00.0-0
   DDC/CI supported: Yes
   Monitor Name: VESA standard monitor
   Input type: Digital
  (Automatically selected)
Reading EDID and initializing DDC/CI at bus pci:02:00.0-0...
I/O warning : failed to load external entity
"/usr/local/share/ddccontrol-db/monitor/DELA010.xml"
Document not parsed successfully.

EDID readings:
        Plug and Play ID: DELA010 [VESA standard monitor]
        Input type: Digital


(snip hard to read, flashing text)

Capabilities:
Raw output: vcp(page0(04 05 06 08 0E 10 12 14(01 04 05 08) 16 18 1A 1E
20 30 3E 60))
Parsed output:
        VCP:
        Type: Unknown

Controls (valid/current/max) [Description - Value name]:
Control 0x04: +/0/1   [???]
Control 0x05: +/0/1   [???]
Control 0x06: +/0/1   [???]
Control 0x08: +/0/1   [???]
Control 0x10: +/1/100   [???]
Control 0x14: +/5/8   [???]
Control 0x16: +/50/100   [???]
Control 0x18: +/50/100   [???]
Control 0x1a: +/50/100   [???]
Control 0x1e: +/0/1   [???]
Control 0x20: +/0/255   [???]
Control 0x60: +/3/3   [???]

^^^^^^^^^

and the Dell monitors already in the database, I created this (DELA010.xml):

vvvvvvvvv

<?xml version=3D"1.0"?>
<monitor name=3D"Dell 2405FPW (Digital)" init=3D"standard">
	<!--- vcp(page0(04 05 06 08 0E 10 12 14(01 04 05 08 0B) 16 18 1A 1E
20 30 3E B0 CC(2 3 4 6 0A) E3)asset_eep(40)mccs_ver(1.0)type(LCD):
INVALID -->
	<caps add=3D"(vcp(04 05 06 08 0E 10 12 14(01 04 05 08) 16 18 1A 1E 20
30 3E 60)"/>
	<controls>
		<control id=3D"colorpreset" address=3D"0x14">
			<value id=3D"warm"  value=3D"0x04"/>
			<value id=3D"srgb"  value=3D"0x05"/>
			<value id=3D"cool"  value=3D"0x08"/>
		</control>

	</controls>
	<include file=3D"VESA"/>
</monitor>

^^^^^^^^^

It seems to work (with the command-line tool, I couldn't get the GUI
to compile---probably a config issue at my end).

Thanks!

--
Alexander


